citation.case_name: Ministers Life & Casualty Union v. Haase

html:
385 U.S. 205

87 S.Ct. 407

17 L.Ed.2d 301

MINISTERS LIFE & CASUALTY UNION
v.
Robert D. HAASE, Commissioner of Insurance, et al.

No. 634.

Supreme Court of the United States

December 5, 1966

Rehearing Denied Jan. 16, 1967.

See 385 U.S. 1033, 87 S.Ct. 739.

Erwin N. Griswold, for appellant.

Bronson C. La Follette, Atty. Gen. of Wisconsin, and E. Weston Wood, Asst. Atty. Gen., for appellees.

Thomas C. Lynch, Atty. Gen., and H. Warren Siegel, Deputy Atty. Gen., for the State of California, amicus curiae.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question.

2

Mr. Justice HARLAN and Mr. Justice STEWART are of the opinion that probable jurisdiction should be noted and the case set for oral argument.

3

Mr. Justice FORTAS took no part in the consideration or decision of this case.
